<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="223" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Hopkins Papers</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The British Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Halifax</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to The British Secretary of State for Foreign
                                    Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Eden</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">most immediate</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-29">December 29,
                                        1941</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>6087. Your telegram no. 7304 first paragraph.<note n="1" xml:id="d223fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_371">p.
                                    371</ref>.</note> Czechoslovakia was included as tenth country
                                in list. Please check decyphering as telegram as sent from here was
                                correct.</p>
                            <p>Luxembourg was however omitted.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>